The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, July 21: Indias forex reserves increased by $4.12 billion for the week ended July 13 to $218.95 billion from $213.83 billion in the previous week. Foreign currency assets increased by $4.11 billion to $211.70 billion during the week, according to figures released by the Reserve Bank. FCAs in dollars include the effect of revaluation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen held in reserves. 

 New Delhi, July 21: Reliance Industries has decided to raise petrol and diesel prices by Rs 1.50 a litre each on Monday. International crude oil prices crossed $77 a barrel this month, forcing the company to raise prices. Currently, 1,300 Reliance pumps sell petrol and diesel.

 Calcutta, July 21: Bangalore-based Real Estate Bank India (Rebi) plans to start operations in Bengal to provide information on real estate transactions under one roof. Rebi has begun operations in Karnataka, Kerala, Tamil Nadu and Andhra Pradesh.




